<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>Hello reddit !</p> <p>I am trying to swap the modeline with the headerline completely.</p> <p>For now I use this snippet of code to have my modeline in my headerline and vice-versa : <code> (defvar og-modeline mode-line-format) (setq-default mode-line-format header-line-format) (setq-default header-line-format og-modeline) </code> This works well except that I&#39;d like to see the empty modeline (as a separator) but it doesn&#39;t show because header-line-format is empty. Is it possible to have an empty string and keep the header-line-format ?</p> <p>My other problem is that lsp-headerline still shows in the real header-line which I don&#39;t want to. Do you know how I could move it down there ?</p> <p>Maybe there is a better way to swap the modeline and the headerline ?</p> <p>Thank you for your help</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/Lefantom55"> /u/Lefantom55 </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/wcnbye/swap_modeline_and_headerline/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/wcnbye/swap_modeline_and_headerline/">[comments]</a></span>